This paper presents a data-driven approach to vehicle motion planning and control in off-road driving scenarios, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also utilizes geographical information system (GIS) and National Centers for Environmental Information datasets, which involves data processing and analysis (cs.AI). The use of sensing and control data for real-time updates suggests the involvement of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Finally, the application of feedback linearization for control falls under the field of control systems (cs.SY).
